extendedInfo.description: Sometimes managing your money feels like running a marathon. But harder.First Commerce is committed to your financial fitness. We keep you equipped with the latest online and mobile technology you need to cross the finish line.ibranchMobile is fast, FREE, and guaranteed secure. Check balances, transfer funds and pay bills right from your mobile device.keywords: Banking, Finance, Bill Payment, Credit Union, Mobile Banking, First Commerce, Florida Commerce, FCCU, First Commerce Credit Union

reviews.title: Ridiculously useful
reviews.comment: If I could give it 4.5 stars I would, because sure it\'s not perfect in navigation. But it\'s always up to the minute accurate, easy to log into, I can do transfers from it instantly.... I can\'t tell you how many times I\'ve been in line at the grocery store and thought \"Uh oh, I don\'t think I have enough money in my checking account... I don\'t want to overdraft and pay a fee!\" Then checked my phone, saw my balance, transferred a few bucks from savings to checking WHILE my groceries were being rung up, and then ran my debit card just in time, dodging that fee. Of course, FCCU only charges $5 for an auto-transfer, but still those add up. What a great bank! And a practically necessary app!
reviews.author: Alan S

reviews.title: Sluggish, missing features, but it does work
reviews.comment: The app is sluggish on my Galaxy Nexus (running stock Android 4.2.1), and its appearance and workflow indicate clearly that this is an iOS app port. It doesn\'t display loan accounts (just checking and savings accounts), and it\'s also missing the ability to deposit checks via the phone\'s camera.  These complaints aside, the features the app *does* offer are functional and get the job done. Checking account balances, transferring funds between accounts (the app does permit transfers to loan accounts despite not showing loan account details) and paying bills can all be done from the app.  It could certainly do with improvements, but it\'s hard to beat the price :)
